message.content: A 'Papilio thoas' is a species of butterfly found in South America. It can reach a wingspan of up to 4 inches (10 cm). The dorsal side of the wings are black with yellow markings, while the ventral side is mainly yellow and black. The wings have a smooth texture and pointed tips. The body of the 'Papilio thoas' is black and slender, with six long legs. It feeds on nectar from a variety of plants and can be found in a range of habitats, from rainforests to open fields. Its striking colors and patterns make it a popular subject for butterfly enthusiasts and collectors.
